<br>
Flanked by the two guards, and trailed by the cleric, she was escorted deeper into Neriak, where both patrolling guards and stationary ones glared at her as she was led past. She couldn't help but glance around at her surroundings a bit, with the occasional chill breeze blowing forth from the caverns. The buildings were a little small for her, but that could be easily fixed with more experience.<br>
<br>
That is, if she ever got out of here.<br>
<br>
She was led into a large, very elegant estate deep in the interior of Neriak, far from the entrance, and even farther from prying eyes. Brought into the main ballroom, she was told to wait until the lord of the manor arrived. Seeing four guards guarding the two doors, each of them decked out in Neriak's finest (and two of them with skeleton companions), she decided that escaping was futile.<br>
<br>
About ten minutes later, the far door opened, and a gentleman entered the chamber. Dressed up in what could only be the adornments of an enchanter, he was very regal and dignified in his walk and look. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rather handsome, too.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> she thought, then mentally kicked herself for it. After all, was she not being held captive in this city by them, and brought here under duplicity and guile?<br>
<br>
All that melted away when he looked at her and said:<br>
<br>
&quot;Welcome to Neriak, Severina, daughter of Xarien... and myself.&quot;<br>
